Key Match Events: The match ended in a 1-1 draw after Congo equalized in the 90th minute.
Elias Mokwana scored a goal in the 33rd minute, but Congo equalized despite defensive lapses by South Africa.
Pre-Game Insights: Congo was expected to lose after a 5-0 defeat in the reverse fixture but managed a draw in their home leg.
Post-Match Reflections: Congo's coach made key changes to the team, contributing to the result.
South Africa's coach Hugo Broos noted the challenge of playing on an artificial pitch.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was significant for South Africa's qualification hopes with a win needed against Uganda next.
Others: The match was part of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification campaign.
